Chairperson of the Eskom board, Jabu Mabuza has made more stunning revelations at the State Capture Commission, saying former Eskom Chief Financial Officer Anoj Singh shared information about a R1.7 billion Absa guarantee for Tegeta with former Regiments’ boss, Eric Wood. Wood was also the CEO at Gupta-linked Trillian Capital. His partners at Regiments accused him of using his company’s accounts for channeling payments to the Guptas. Mabuza says Absa pulled out of the transaction when it began to attract media attention. LISTEN BELOW: <a href="https://iono.fm/e/659146">Content hosted by iono.fm</a> 